zboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=569.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Soloing at Level 49... Where and Howto...</span><hr size=1> Cobalt scar is where I soloed from 48 - 53.  You need to get good faction with CoV before you go there.  Do this by killing (or tagging) Dire wolfs and various giants in GD and Kael.<br><br>In CS the loot is quite good, you can single or quad kite wyverns aor drakes.  Watch out for the named wyvern and the named drake.  Do not try the otters yet.<br><br>If you want to you can also try the enchanters, they are a bit more exciting. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uchiriko37.showPublicProfile?language=EN>chiriko37</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(9/9/02 8:12:54 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=569.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Soloing at Level 49... Where and Howto...</span><hr size=1> 49-50 are the real hell levels for wizards, IMHO. we don't have an efficient enough AE to quad through these levels so you're going to be stuck grouping and single pulling. sounds like you've been single-pulling already, so maybe that's not so bad for you. I found xp when pretty quick and I was able to get a group occaionsally hunting stuff in DL. lots of mobs there are still blue at 50 and you can get clarity and sow for free pretty much anytime you need it. at 49/50 you can also solo mobs in BW and skyfire pretty easily.<br><br>-Chiriko <p><center>Chiriko, lvl 56 Evoker, Innoruuk<br>Lux et Veritas<br><img src="http://new.comfluent.net/images/chiriko2.jpg"></center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/urashakra.showPublicProfile?language=EN>rashakra</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(9/9/02 6:45:27 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=569.topic&index=3>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.myezboard.com/projects/ezboard/ezboard_userimages/forsakenlords/images/selfpic.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Soloing at Level 49... Where and Howto...</span><hr size=1> Stuns, root, and ice comet really made Nagafen's Lair a great place to get xp for me.  It had to be empty for the most part tho. <p>Rashakra N'Faria<BR>Evoker (58)<BR>Tribunal<BR><BR><BR><BR><A HREF=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=108699 target=new>Magelo Profile</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ugarielhalliwell.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Gariel Halliwell</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(9/10/02 5:42:24 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=569.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Soloing at Level 49... Where and Howto...</span><hr size=1> You could try Cyndreela (sic) the Erudite necromancer that hangs out in front of the fear portal.  She will drop from two ice comets and is really easy to take out before she summons a pet.  She is not on a faction, drops gems frequently and has about a 5 minute respawn.<br><br>And, if you run into trouble, can always zone into Fear =)<br><br>Also, if you have good manapool, should be able to solo in Skyfire.  I was in there for level 52.  Plus, with the changes to the cleric epic, you should be able to find a group in there if needed or at least an available rez for promise of future pearlescent shards you find.<br><br>Mistress Gariel Halliwell<br>Sorcerer of The Hand, Xev <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uianblood.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ianblood</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(9/10/02 5:50:10 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=569.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Soloing at 49</span><hr size=1> Any particular mobs in Skyfire ? Any particular areas ?<br><br>Anything that should be avoided?  Any info is appreciated, been wanting to go there for some time. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ubayler.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bayler</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(9/19/02 4:09:47 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=569.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Soloing at 49</span><hr size=1> Fire seems to be useless in Skyfire, so you probably can't start until Ice Comet at 49.  It works better than Rend.<br><br>Wyverns, Gnawers, and Drakes are probably the best Skyfire targets.  Wurms have more hit points, and a *huge* hit range - you might not have enough space to cast your spells.<br><br>The most annoying mob in Skyfire - for everyone - is the Chromadrac.  They have an AE dispell proc.  If all goes well their kitable without letting them in range.  But it sure would suck to lose a precious KEI or SoW if you let one get a little too close.<br><br>If anything you kill drops a nodrop pearl shard (I'm not sure of the exact name), you'll score major points with local clerics by giving them a loc. <p><B>Bayler</B> 56th rank Swashbuckler - <I>Xev</I><BR><B>Tessally</B> 50th flicker Nun of Solusek Ro - <I>Xev</I><BR></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/udaxilsolshok.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Daxil Solshok</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(10/1/02 7:09:40 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=569.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://daxil.htmlplanet.com/images/eq000093.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Soloing at Level 49... Where and Howto...</span><hr size=1> When I wasn't going on TOFS or Naggy/Vox raids I soloed pretty effectively to 50 in DL. Just go to the Nexus and grab a KEI. About 1 in 3 MOBs still con blue in DL at this point. The best place to solo kite is SE of Karnors along the dirt strip near the woods. No groups are here and the MOBs are fairly spread out. With KEI you gain a gold about once an hour when single pulling...probably faster if you use Circle of Force and try and do two at a time.<br><br>For those with reservations about spending the pp on KEI...why do you think we make money off ports? It's so you can afford the KEI. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/umuklestikk.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mukle Stikk</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(10/4/02 2:04:20 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=569.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Soloing at Level 49... Where and Howto...</span><hr size=1> Spirocs in TD is great until about 51-52.  Get KEI and hit TD with CoF you can kill them fairly easily.  I didn't find levels slow until 51  =(<br><br>Ephraim the Channeler <p>Mukle Stikk<BR>Grandmaster (retired)<BR><BR><img src=http://www3.sympatico.ca/deadpool/muklesig.jpg></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uashtaytherogue.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ashtay the Rogue</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Visitor</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(10/16/02 3:01:09 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=569.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Soloing at Level 49... Where and Howto...</span><hr size=1> Seafuries in OOT is great exp from 48-51.  Either solo or with a pet class friend.  Beasties is my partner of choice here but any will work. <p><img src="http://thack.net/ashtay1.jpg"></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm19.showPrevMessage?topicID=569.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm19.showNextMessage?topicID=569.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=569.topic&index=9><img src=http://www.graffe.com/messageboard/add_reply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><t